{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0590c7ce-93f0-4473-b04a-f980c31b126a","content":"In .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are replaced by **`Window` lifecycle events**. You either subclass `Window` or subscribe to events on it.\n\n**Option 1 — Override in a custom `Window`:**\n\n```csharp\npublic class MyWindow : Window\n{\n    public MyWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }\n\n    protected override void OnCreated()    { /* was OnStart  */ }\n    protected override void OnStopped()    { /* was OnSleep  */ }\n    protected override void OnResumed()    { /* was OnResume */ }\n}\n```\n\nThen in your `App` class:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n    => new MyWindow(new MainPage());\n```\n\n**Option 2 — Subscribe to events inline:**\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = new Window(new MainPage());\n    window.Created  += (s, e) => { /* OnStart  */ };\n    window.Stopped  += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep  */ };\n    window.Resumed  += (s, e) => { /* OnResume */ };\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Quick mapping:**\n\n| Xamarin.Forms | MAUI Window |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart()` | `OnCreated()` / `Created` |\n| `OnSleep()` | `OnStopped()` / `Stopped` |\n| `OnResume()` | `OnResumed()` / `Resumed` |\n\nThere are also `OnActivated`/`OnDeactivated` for finer-grained focus tracking, and `ConfigureLifecycleEvents()` in `MauiProgram.cs` for platform-specific hooks (e.g., Android `OnActivityResult`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2e5e5fd7-91bf-4500-9ed2-cef3eaa13243","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle events from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` in your `Application` subclass.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the equivalent is to use the `Window` lifecycle events or the `ILifecycleEvents` interface. Specifically:\n\n- The `Application` class in MAUI still has `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` virtual methods that you can override, but the recommended approach is to use the `Window` lifecycle events.\n\n\n- The `Window` class exposes lifecycle events like `Created`, `Activated`, `Deactivated`, `Stopped`, `Resumed`, and `Destroying` that you can subscribe to.\n- You can override `CreateWindow()` in your `Application` class to access and hook into these window lifecycle events.\n- Alternatively, you can use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs` for platform-specific lifecycle handling, or create a custom `Window` subclass to override the lifecycle methods directly.","outputTokens":947,"requestId":"A420:32AFE6:5F9E640:6817DC1:69F00531"},"id":"31493e04-6381-47bf-b8e4-f2e9e0ca03c3","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:54:27.817Z","parentId":"c019b69d-ce5f-4a47-be77-eb7ccb318e48"}
